<center>
	<BR><BR><BR>

<font size=+1><B>
Testing Multiple Gene Interactions by the Ordered Combinatorial Partitioning Method in Case-Control Studies
</font></B>
</center>

<BR><BR>
<BR>
<UL>

OCP (<font color=red>Ordered Combinatorial Partitioning</font>) is a free software along with the paper:
Testing Multiple Gene Interactions by the Ordered Combinatorial Partitioning Method in Case-Control Studies. <br><br>

OCP can be used to detect multiple gene interaction. Our OCP method extend the powerful
<a href="http://www.multifactordimensionalityreduction.org/">Multifactor Dimensionality Reduction (MDR)</a> method to
a more flexible framework which significantly improves the power of MDR in many common cases. We also proposed new
evaluation measures based on GEVD as alternative to cross-validation consistency and prediction error in MDR, which
accelerates the interaction order determinant and reduces the time cost for p-value calculation. <br><br><br>

<UL>
1. <em><font color=red>OCP v1.0 beta </font></em>has been released on 2009-7-28. <br>
&nbsp &nbsp Download the OCP program <a href="./OCP_v1.0_beta.rar">here</a>. <br>
&nbsp &nbsp Please <a href="./README">readme</a> the first time you run it. <br><br>
2. Supplementary material <a href="./ocp-suppl.pdf">[PDF]</a>.
</UL>
<br><br>
OCP is available as free software under the terms of GNU General Public License. <br>
The source codes written in C++ are available from the authors upon request. <br><br>

OCP is still a beta version now, if you think you have found a bug, or have any problem, <br>
please contact me by <a href="mailto:zhangh.ustc@gmail.com"><img src="../img/emaillogo.png" style="border:0"></a>

</UL>
